Chapter 2: The Glitch in the Medicine
The Scene: Leon’s apartment. It’s a cramped, one-bedroom unit in the "Grey Blocks," where the air is thick with the hum of the city’s mana-generators.
Leon sat at the small kitchen table, the [Void Fragment] hovering just above his palm. It looked like a piece of shattered obsidian, but the edges blurred and shifted as if the air itself couldn't decide if the object was actually there.
"Leon? Is that you?" Liora’s voice came from the bedroom, followed by a heavy, rattling cough.
"Yeah, Li. I’m just... getting your dose ready," Leon called back. He looked at the vial on the table. It was Low-Grade Mana-Suppressant, a murky grey liquid that barely did anything but keep her from seizing. It cost him half a month’s wages.
He reached out. As his fingers touched the glass, the red static returned to his vision.
> [ITEM DETECTED: Low-Grade Mana-Suppressant]
> [QUALITY: Poor (12% Efficiency)]
> [COMPATIBLE DATA DETECTED: Void Fragment (Corrupted)]
> [INITIATE OVERWRITE? WARNING: RESULT IS UNSTABLE]
> 
Leon hesitated. If he messed this up, he could kill her. But at 74% saturation, the "safe" medicine was already failing. He gritted his teeth and thought one word: Apply.
The Void Fragment didn't melt; it snapped into the vial. The grey liquid turned a deep, crystalline violet. The glass hissed, frost forming on the outside as the "Logic" of the medicine was rewritten.
> [OVERWRITE SUCCESSFUL]
> [NEW ITEM: Glitched Essence (Rank: ???)]
> [EFFECT: Restores 'System Harmony'. Reduces Saturation by 5%.]
> [SIDE EFFECT: Triggers 'Mana-Sensory Awakening' in the consumer.]
> 
"Five percent..." Leon whispered. It wasn't a cure, but it was a miracle. The side effect worried him, but he had no choice.
He walked into the bedroom. Liora looked smaller than she had this morning, her skin pale against the threadbare sheets. He lifted her head and helped her swallow the violet liquid.
For a moment, she went stiff. Her eyes flew open—not their usual brown, but for a split second, glowing with the same violet static as Leon’s hook. Then, she exhaled, the tension leaving her body as her breathing smoothed out.
"Leon..." she whispered, her voice stronger. "I feel... I feel like I can see the wind."
Leon’s heart sank even as it soared. He had saved her for today, but he had changed her. He realized then that the more he used his "Glitch," the more he would pull Liora into the dangerous world of the Awakened.

